  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The aims of this three-year study are to explore the protective and risk factors of
      resilience in colorectal cancer patients, and examine the effect of the resilience
      model-based care plan in reducing fear of recurrence and GI symptom distress and improving
      quality of life in newly diagnosed colorectal cancer (CRC) patients.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Develop and evaluate the effect of a resilience model-based total care plan on reducing fear
      of recurrence and GI symptom distress and improving quality of life (QOL) in this population.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
